13 §3305. External central institutional review board; local review
14 A. The requirements of this Section apply regardless of participation in
15 department-coordinated activity.
16 B. When an external central institutional review board is designated as the
17 institutional review board of record or has approved the covered clinical project, a
18 research entity shall not require separate local institutional review board approval or
19 conduct duplicate local institutional review board ethical review. Nothing in this
20 Subsection shall limit lawful local review preserved by this Section.
21 C. For a first-in-human clinical trial, Phase I clinical trial, early-feasibility
22 device trial, or dose-escalation trial, a research entity shall rely on an external central
23 institutional review board as the institutional review board of record where permitted
24 by law and where a federally compliant reliance arrangement is available, unless
25 external central institutional review board reliance is prohibited by federal law, state
26 law, or binding federal award condition, or the sponsor or its authorized
27 representative states in writing that the research entity's institutional review board
28 serve as the institutional review board of record.
